flowRoot.flowPara: Search bar slides down when the search button is pressed or with the Ctrl+F shortcut
The search is started once the user stops typing
If it takes more than two seconds to return results, a spinner is shown
Results are returned from the current location
Search results are presented in chunks - you load each one as you scroll down
Pressing the clear button resets the view to the original content but keeps the search bar visible
Ctrl+F or pressing the search button resets the content and hides the search bar
Drop down allows filters to be applied.
The first item is highlighted, in order to indicate that the return key will preview it. However, this item is not selected.
Labels indicate when a search filter is applied. Selecting the label removes it.
Filters are applied when the done button is pressed.
